		"AbilityTooltips"
		{
			"special_bonus_cast_range_100"		"Considering nature of Bane's spells, the hero wants to stay away from fight to avoid being focused and cast range helps dealing with that"
			"special_bonus_armor_7"		"Armor works well if you're going for more of a core-ish playstyle and planning to tank in fights (which works fine when you're going for a hybrid way)"
			"special_bonus_unique_bane_4"		"Works well in combination with Mjolnir and buffs your hero. Altho it works only during fights and it's unreliable"
			"special_bonus_exp_boost_40"		"Works every time and tends to be a more reliable alternative unless you're already stomping"
			"special_bonus_movement_speed_50"		"+50 flat movement speed is a lot and it's reliable and easy to get use of"
			"special_bonus_unique_bane_3"		"Great if you're going for more of an utility way"
			"special_bonus_unique_bane_2"		"...but you picked offlane Bane not to be a disabler, right? Increasing your damage output on Brain Sap effectively turns the spell into poor man's Laguna Blade. The spell is extremely strong when you're playing tank Bane and have aghs"
			"bane_fiends_grip"		"One of the strongest disables in the game. You can use it to setup kills with your team early on, but later into the game it may be better to either initiate with it or hold it off since you're most likely to play as a tanky frontlaner which increases your chances of being interrupted mid-ult"
			"bane_nightmare"		"You can use it to both harass opponents early on and setup kills. It can also be used for it's 1sec invulnerability after cast which can save you or your allies (or your enemies) from a projectile or a spell (like X-Mark)"
			"bane_brain_sap"		"Poor man's Laguna Blade, pure damage nuke and heal. Makes a better hit-trader out of you and a good tank"
			"bane_enfeeble"		"You can also use if just to get longer duration on effects (slows, stuns) from your team and increase kill potential"
		}
